# BuildKit uses this file (named for its Dockerfile) instead of the repo-root .dockerignore
# when building ci-builder with context = repo root. The root .dockerignore is the nextcloud
# image's `* + whitelist` and would bake nothing here. We bake the whole platform tree, minus
# VCS metadata and any app/generated trees (apps/ is gitignored so usually absent in the CI
# checkout, but guard regardless).
.git
apps
**/.build
**/.dist
**/node_modules
**/vendor
**/*.tar.gz
